  "stratum": "positive-control",
  "canonical_definition": "Gradient descent is a first-order iterative optimization algorithm that minimizes a differentiable function by repeatedly stepping in the direction of the negative gradient at the current point, with step size controlled by a learning rate.",
  "near_neighbors": [
